<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php3'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> The 10 best cards of Realms<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(3.14)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10885'>Wouter "Venator" Neyt</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10885&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> June 15, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> I mean this article as a short view on the new set and as a prediction of what new cards will be used in new decks, but also as akind of poll. When you review this article, base your rating on how your view corresponds with mine and include your own top 10. Now, here we go.<br />
<br />
10. Tower of Barad-dur<br />
Together with the Isengard fortress, the best cards in their kind for the shadow. This one doesn&#39;t need a special theme to include in your deck (although you can expect some Sauron discard decks are going to show up). You can bet to rid minimum 4 cards with these, it will disencourage your opponent to move twice, and the discarding happens before the maneuver, so that are a lot of crucial cards to be able to get rid off.<br />
<br />
9. Citadel of Minas Tirith<br />
The best fortress for the free peoples, the fortress for the Elves is also going to see a lot of play, but is very easy to get rid of (vulnerable to condition and ally removing). This card though supports very well the decks out there right now: you exert your gondor men to get rid of minions, in archery or in skirmishes, but you need an ARV  or something else to move twice. This condition heals your men, right after they have done the job.<br />
<br />
8. Isengard smith<br />
4 twilight, can get rid of two weapons, all possesions if you spot five companions. All you have to do is keep him clean of wounds untill the regroup phase. In the worst case it is cancelling legolas game text. Now if only we could cancel directed archery...<br />
<br />
7. Isengard warrior<br />
O yeah, this one cancels the directed archery if you can spot another isengard orc. That&#39;s good, he can possibly deal two exertion tokens on every companion, all you have to do is spot 3 wounds on the ring-bearer and keep him clear of wounds untill the regroup. Now if only...hey wait you don&#39;t have directed archery. People will stop bothering Frodo with thror&#39;s map-reading and using his sting and that&#39;s always good...<br />
<br />
6. The palantir of orthanc<br />
Talk about knocking crucial cards out of your opponent&#39;s hand. If he played a lot, this could mean you even stop him, with you playing only one big uruk. Talk about card-advantage. Plus you prevent your opponent from playing maneuver and skirmish events.<br />
<br />
5. Saruman, keeper of Isengard<br />
It&#39; three goblin armories in one card. It actually solves the problem of the archery phase. and it makes your Uruk&#39;s fierce. Fierce is two wounds, damage +1 is two wounds but together it&#39;s four wounds. What a killer combo! everyone, replace your spies of saruman and you uruk rampage with this card. Because if your are willing to pay three to make one Uruk fierce, I think you will not fall over the extra one to make them all fierce. Sorry if the expression I used does&#39;nt exist in English.<br />
<br />
4. Vilya, Elrond&#39;s ring<br />
Two wounds to get rid for any condition for a short time: goblin swarms, blade tips, black breaths, expensive conditions...Best used one the new Elrond, but the extra vitality is nice for the card-drawing engine Elrond.<br />
<br />
3.Nenya, Galadriel&#39;s Ring<br />
Discard two cards (probably shadow) to get two new ones (hopefully free peoples)? That&#39;s good and it doesn&#39;t cost you exertion so with the extra vitality, she is pritty safe untill you want to use your mirror and so planning for a triple or quadruple move.<br />
<br />
2.Galadriel, lady of the golden wood<br />
Heals an elf every turn. Do I have to say more? Except for that her site-playing ability will probably rock in the set of the second movie.<br />
<br />
1. Elrond,herald to Gil-galad<br />
Heals a companion every turn. Do I have to say more? This card seems very basic but it just rocks. Thinking the old Elrond is better. This card can be played without playing Gandalf or Elves. <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?id=3787&view=1&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
